      <h1 class='title'>Digital Curriculum</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 09 January 2003 vol 397 c16WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_16ws' title='Col. 16WS &mdash; HC Deb 09 January 2003 vol 397 c16WS' name='column_16ws' href='#column_16ws' rel='bookmark'>16WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0397P0-04110'>
        <a name='S6CV0397P0_20030109_CWS_6'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-tessa-jowell' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0397P0_20030109_CWS_6' title='Link to this speech by Ms Tessa Jowell' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-tessa-jowell" title="Ms Tessa Jowell">The Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport (Tessa Jowell)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0397P0-04110">I have today placed my decision, in the form of a letter to Gavyn Davies of 8 January and its accompanying schedule, on the BBC's application for approval of a licence-fee funded digital curriculum service in the Libraries of both Houses.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-04111">I have approved the application, and have attached specific conditions to the approval to ensure that the service makes a positive contribution to a varied and competitive industry in education software.</p><p id="S6CV0397P0-04112">The service against the approval will be reviewed within two years of its launch.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
